	function [Xnum, Xden] = S_2_Z(G, Szeros, Spoles)		% 	Computes the impedance in rational form corresponding to a 	%	reflectance in terms of the poles and zeros of S. 	% 	Toolbox for ANALOG FILTERS USING MATLAB 		% 	Author: 		Lars Wanhammar 2007-06-25	% 	Modified by: 		% 	Copyright:		by authors - not released for commercial use	% 	Version: 		1	% 	Known bugs:	 	% 	Report bugs to:	Wanhammar@gmail.com	%	To improve:		Check that S is a true reflection function			N = length(Spoles);		SnumPoly = G*ROOTS_2_POLY(Szeros);	SdenPoly = ROOTS_2_POLY(Spoles);	Xnum = POLYADD(SnumPoly, SdenPoly);	Xden = POLYSUB(SdenPoly, SnumPoly);	 	